# Aurum style rules

## Scope discipline
- Change only what the user asked.
- Keep business flow unchanged unless explicitly requested.
- Avoid touching keywords, DB schema, publishing behavior, or content formatting when task is LLM-layer only.

## LLM integration
- Route all model calls through one abstraction layer.
- Do not hardcode provider-specific logic inside article/domain logic.
- Prefer provider config from `.env` over inline constants.
- Keep fallback behavior explicit and visible in logs.

## Reliability
- Preserve current error handling behavior unless task requests otherwise.
- Validate generated JSON before downstream usage.
- Print actionable warnings when provider/model fails or falls back.

## Editing safety
- Do not rewrite existing prompts unless asked.
- Do not remove unrelated code during refactors.
- Keep file edits minimal and surgical.
